        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 24 at 10:46AM MST by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>A band of snow along a cold front is currently making its way
through Southwestern Montana. As this snowfall band pushes through
the area, be prepared for a sudden drop in visibility, suddenly
gusty winds, and a potential for a flash freeze as temperatures
rapidly drop once the snow begins. If you will be traveling,
particularly on Interstate 90 between Homestake Pass near Butte
and Bozeman Pass, remain alert for any Snow Squall Warnings and
for sudden changes in road conditions. Ensure your headlights are
on and give yourself extra following distance.
</description>
